\subsection{Description of the Data
Resource}\label{description-of-the-data-resource}

The Johns Hopkins Corona-virus Resource Center established a new
standard for infectious disease tracking by publicly providing pandemic
data in near real-time. It began on January 22, 2020, as the COVID-19
Dashboard, operated by the Center for Systems Science and Engineering
(CSSE) and the Applied Physics Laboratory. This is the data set that
will be used for this analysis. The Corona-virusResource Center ceased
its data collection as of March 2022. Further information can be found
at \url{https://coronavirus.jhu.edu/}.

\subsubsection{Objective}\label{objective}

The objective of this analysis is to explore the COVID-19 data set from
Johns Hopkins University. The data set contains information on confirmed
cases, deaths, and recoveries for countries around the world. The
analysis will focus on visualizing the data, identifying trends, and
gaining insights into the spread of the virus.

\subsubsection{Data Collection}\label{data-collection}

The data set used in this analysis is sourced from the Johns Hopkins
University Center for Systems Science and Engineering (JHU CSSE)
COVID-19 Data Repository. We are concerned with the time series data for
confirmed cases, deaths, and recoveries at the global level and for the
United States. This data can be found at the following location:
\url{https://github.com/CSSEGISandData/COVID-19/tree/master/csse_covid_19_data/csse_covid_19_time_series}.

\subsubsection{Data Description}\label{data-description}

The following is a list of the data sets that we downloaded from the
Johns Hopkins University Center for Systems Science and Engineering (JHU
CSSE) COVID-19 Data Repository:

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  global\_confirmed\_transformed: Time series data for confirmed
  COVID-19 cases at the global level.
\item
  global\_deaths: Time series data for COVID-19 deaths at the global
  level.
\item
  global\_recovered: Time series data for COVID-19 recoveries at the
  global level.
\item
  us\_confirmed: Time series data for confirmed COVID-19 cases in the
  United States.
\item
  us\_deaths: Time series data for COVID-19 deaths in the United States.
\end{itemize}

\subsection{Data Cleaning and
Transformation}\label{data-cleaning-and-transformation}

We will change the Global data sets (confirmed, deaths, and recovered)
to have the same columns: Province\_State, Country\_Region, date, cases,
deaths, and recovered. We will also change the US data sets (confirmed
and deaths) by renaming Long\_ to Long to match the Global data sets.
The last change will be to rename Admin2 to County in the US data sets.
These changes will create a common structure for all data sets.

\begin{Shaded}

\CommentTok{\# Function to check and rename columns if necessary}
\NormalTok{check\_and\_rename }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}} \ControlFlowTok{function}\NormalTok{(df, old\_names, new\_names) \{}
    \ControlFlowTok{for}\NormalTok{ (i }\ControlFlowTok{in} \FunctionTok{seq\_along}\NormalTok{(old\_names)) \{}
        \ControlFlowTok{if}\NormalTok{ (old\_names[i] }\SpecialCharTok{\%in\%} \FunctionTok{names}\NormalTok{(df)) \{}
\NormalTok{            df }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ df }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
                \FunctionTok{rename}\NormalTok{(}\SpecialCharTok{!!}\NormalTok{new\_names[i] }\SpecialCharTok{:=} \SpecialCharTok{!!}\NormalTok{old\_names[i])}
\NormalTok{        \}}
\NormalTok{    \}}
    \FunctionTok{return}\NormalTok{(df)}
\NormalTok{\}}

    \FunctionTok{mutate}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{deaths\_per\_mill =}\NormalTok{ deaths }\SpecialCharTok{*} \FloatTok{1e+06}\SpecialCharTok{/}\NormalTok{Population) }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}

\CommentTok{\# Get the total cases, deaths, and recoveries for the US Step 1: Get the max}
\CommentTok{\# date for each \textquotesingle{}Province\_State\textquotesingle{}, \textquotesingle{}Country\_Region\textquotesingle{}}
\NormalTok{us\_by\_county\_state\_max\_date }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ us\_by\_county\_state }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
    \FunctionTok{group\_by}\NormalTok{(Province\_State, Country\_Region) }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
    \FunctionTok{summarize}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{max\_date =} \FunctionTok{max}\NormalTok{(}\FunctionTok{as.Date}\NormalTok{(date, }\AttributeTok{format =} \StringTok{"\%m/\%d/\%y"}\NormalTok{)), }\AttributeTok{.groups =} \StringTok{"drop"}\NormalTok{)}

\CommentTok{\# Step 2: Join the max dates with the original data to get case counts on those}
\CommentTok{\# dates}
\NormalTok{us\_by\_county\_state\_max\_cases }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ us\_by\_county\_state }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
    \FunctionTok{mutate}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{date =} \FunctionTok{as.Date}\NormalTok{(date, }\AttributeTok{format =} \StringTok{"\%m/\%d/\%y"}\NormalTok{)) }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
    \FunctionTok{inner\_join}\NormalTok{(us\_by\_county\_state\_max\_date, }\AttributeTok{by =} \FunctionTok{c}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"Province\_State"}\NormalTok{, }\StringTok{"Country\_Region"}\NormalTok{,}
        \AttributeTok{date =} \StringTok{"max\_date"}\NormalTok{))}

\CommentTok{\# Step 3: Summarize to get total cases, deaths, and recoveries by}
\CommentTok{\# \textquotesingle{}Province\_State\textquotesingle{}, \textquotesingle{}Country\_Region\textquotesingle{}}
\NormalTok{total\_us\_cases\_deaths }\OtherTok{\textless{}{-}}\NormalTok{ us\_by\_county\_state\_max\_cases }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
    \FunctionTok{group\_by}\NormalTok{(Province\_State, Country\_Region) }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
    \FunctionTok{summarize}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{total\_cases =} \FunctionTok{sum}\NormalTok{(cases), }\AttributeTok{total\_deaths =} \FunctionTok{sum}\NormalTok{(deaths), }\AttributeTok{.groups =} \StringTok{"drop"}\NormalTok{) }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
    \FunctionTok{mutate}\NormalTok{(}\AttributeTok{total\_cases =} \FunctionTok{format}\NormalTok{(total\_cases, }\AttributeTok{big.mark =} \StringTok{","}\NormalTok{), }\AttributeTok{total\_deaths =} \FunctionTok{format}\NormalTok{(total\_deaths,}
        \AttributeTok{big.mark =} \StringTok{","}\NormalTok{))}

\CommentTok{\# Display the result using kable}
\NormalTok{total\_us\_cases\_deaths }\SpecialCharTok{\%\textgreater{}\%}
    \FunctionTok{kable}\NormalTok{(}\StringTok{"html"}\NormalTok{, }\AttributeTok{caption =} \StringTok{"Total U.S. cases and deaths by Province\_State and Country\_Region."}\NormalTok{)}
\end{Highlighting}
